<worksheet >
    <title>TF-2 Graphing Trigonometric Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete all seven problems to earn M. Complete problem 7 and any four other problems to earn P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <p>Given <m>f(x)=-3-\frac{5}{2}\sin\left(\frac{8\pi x}{5}+\frac{8\pi}{5}\right)</m></p>
    <exercise workspace="0.75in"><statement><p>State the amplitude.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="0.75in"><statement><p>State the period.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="0.75in"><statement><p>State the phase shift.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="0.75in"><statement><p>State the vertical shift.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in"><statement><p>State the five key points of the principal period.</p></statement></exercise>
  </page>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in"><statement><p>State the intercepts.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in"><statement><p>Graph <m>f(x)</m> on the interval <m>[0,2\pi]</m></p></statement></exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>